er. It feels like a solid approach to validate functionality, but I wonder if I've covered all edge cases. I'll make sure to be thorough!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering contract attributes**\\n\\nI'm looking at the Version typed attribute, which allows for ordering and comparison. There's also the existing qualified comparison. I’m wondering if tests should enhance dynamic access coverage, but that’s not relevant since the existing class is only ContractNamespace. I’m thinking about inspecting the issue further. However, it seems like adding a single test for a versionless contract name requirement that matches all versions could be an acceptable solution.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating code adjustments**\\n\\nI'm considering adding “unversioned requirement matches all versions” so that the client can retrieve Version objects. I’m not sure if an import is necessary here, though. Maybe I can use the edit insert method after contractRequirementUses? I think that could be okay. I'm weighing my options carefully here to ensure everything fits together seamlessly and works as intended. I wonder if there's a better approach I might be missing.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_XCwrufz0xp1u6qurQYQ3nY8Y|fc_0a4a8766bf7374d20169f72eb5feac819392f014a5e149b0e5", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.osgi/org.osgi.namespace.contract/1.0.0/src/test/java/org_osgi/org_osgi_namespace_contract/Org_osgi_namespace_contractTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "    @Test\n    void optionalActiveRequirementIsKeptSeparateFromResolveTimeRequirement() {\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void nameOnlyContractRequirementMatchesEveryVersionOfThatContract() throws Exception {\n        SyntheticResource resource = new SyntheticResource();\n        Capability servletFive = resource.addContractCapability(JAKARTA_SERVLET_CONTRACT, \"5.0.0\", Map.of());\n        Capability servletSix = resource.addContractCapability(JAKARTA_SERVLET_CONTRACT, \"6.0.0\", Map.of());\n        resource.addContractCapability(JAX_RS_CONTRACT, \"3.1.0\", Map.of());\n        Requirement requirement = resource.addRequirement(\n                ContractNamespace.CONTRACT_NAMESPACE,\n                Map.of(Namespace.REQUIREMENT_FILTER_DIRECTIVE,\n                        \"(\" + ContractNamespace.CONTRACT_NAMESPACE + \"=\" + JAKARTA_SERVLET_CONTRACT + \")\"),\n                Map.of());\n\n        assertThat(contractCapabilitiesMatchingFilter(resource, requirement)).containsExactly(servletFive, servletSix);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void optionalActiveRequirementIsKeptSeparateFromResolveTimeRequirement() {\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1560, "output": 2170, "cacheRead": 21504, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 25234, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777807000704, "responseId": "resp_0a4a8766bf7374d20169f72e9926748193bba1e58a1a22883d"}}
